\Ser"pent*ry\
Serpentry is a noun generally defined as a winding like a serpent's, or a place inhabited or infested by serpents.

Also, serpentry may pertain to any act or motion of a serpent or serpent like creature. These acts, such as slithering, climbing, eat, drinking, killing, sleeping, or constricting can be classified as serpentry behavior. An example of this is a corn snake, who may "slither around all serpantry like."